38.17. tanti munerla, i.e. tanti operis. The two expressions are united in Cicero Tusc. l, 28, 70: moderator tanti operis et muneris: and below II, 35, 90: architectum tanti operis tantique muneris. Munus is especially used ol public buildings, as temples or theatres, constructed at private expense.
